14. to blow hot and cold→see hot 

15. blow someone a kiss→see kiss 

16. to blow the whistle→see whistle NOUN USES blow /bləʊ/ (blows) V 

1. N-COUNT If someone receives a blow , they are hit with a fist or weapon. (用拳或武器的) 击打 

例： He went to the hospital after a blow to the face. 他脸上挨了一拳后就去了医院。 

2. N-COUNT If something that happens is a blow to someone or something, it is very upsetting, disappointing, or damaging to them. 打击 

例： That ruling comes as a blow to environmentalists. 那项规定对环境保护主义者是一个打击。 

